🔹 Step 1: Download Flutter SDK
Go to 👉 https://flutter.dev/docs/get-started/install/windows
Download Flutter SDK (zip file)
Extract it to:
C:\flutter
🔹 Step 2: Set Environment Path
Press Windows + S → search "Environment Variables"
Click Edit system environment variables
Click Environment Variables
In System Variables → find Path → click Edit
Click New and add:
C:\flutter\bin
Click OK → OK → OK
🔹 Step 3: Check Installation

Open Command Prompt (cmd):

flutter doctor

👉 It will show missing components (Android Studio, etc.)

🔹 Step 4: Install Android Studio
Download from 👉 https://developer.android.com/studio
Install normally
Open Android Studio
🔹 Step 5: Install Android SDK

Inside Android Studio:

Click More Actions → SDK Manager
Install:
Android SDK
Platform Tools
Emulator
🔹 Step 6: Accept Licenses

In CMD:

flutter doctor --android-licenses

Press y for all

🔹 Step 7: Verify Setup
flutter doctor

👉 All should show ✔ (green ticks)

🔹 Step 8: Create Flutter Project
flutter create myapp
cd myapp
🔹 Step 9: Run App
flutter run

👉 It will open emulator or browser

✅ 📌 Output
Flutter installed successfully
Android Studio configured
First app runs successfully
✅ 🧠 Conclusion (Write in Exam)

👉 Successfully installed Flutter SDK and configured Android Studio on Windows. The environment is ready for developing Flutter applications.
